      "instruction": "<p>Once the tomatoes have started to soften, remove the pan from the heat and add the<strong> spinach </strong>with your <strong>sundried tomato pesto</strong>, <strong>roasted garlic paste </strong>and<strong> chicken stock mix</strong></p><p>Return the pan to the heat, stir it all together and cook for 2-3 min or until the spinach has wilted</p><p>Once wilted, add<strong> </strong>your <strong>crème fraiche</strong> with a splash of <strong>cold water</strong> and cook for a final 1-2 min or until the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!) – this is your <strong>creamy sundried tomato pesto & chicken sauce</strong></p>",
